<p color="yellow">Breeze::OS Installer Setup -- Package Source</p>
<p>
You selected a <b>network</b> source for <b>Breeze::OS</b> packages.<br>
On saving your settings, the <b>selected</b> server will be contacted,<br>and the <b>specified desktop file</b> retrieved.<br>
The <font color="#33FB01"><b>netinstall</b></font> desktop file is used<br>to <b>replicate</b> the server's installation onto this computer.<br>
An <font color="#33FB01"><b>unattended</b></font> installation can be performed by specifying<br>the appropriate settings at <b>boot time</b> on the <b>boot prompt</b>.<br>
      e.g. boot frontend=batch server=192.168.2.1 install=replicate.seq<br>
	  See the file <b>/etc/packager/unattended.txt</b>.
</p>
<p>
Click on <a href="action=apply"><img width="16" height="16" src="install/images/apply.png"></a> to <b>Save your settings</b>.<br>
Click on <a href="action=continue"><img width="16" height="16" src="install/images/next.png"></a> to <b>Continue</b>.
</p>
